sequenceDiagram
    actor Creator as Admin or Authorized Submitter
    actor Reviewer as Admin
    actor Gate as Guard
    participant UI as JavaFX Event Screens
    participant API as EventRequestController
    participant Service as EventRequestService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Creator->>UI: Enter schema-defined header and positive-quantity manifest rows
    UI->>API: POST /api/v1/event-requests
    API->>Service: create request
    Service->>DB: Read event_request_max_duration_days
    Service->>Service: Validate document, dates, duration, manifest
    Service->>DB: INSERT request and devices as approved
    API-->>UI: Approved request

    opt Manually queued or returned request
        Reviewer->>API: PUT /{id}/approve, /return, or /reject
        API->>Service: Validate role and required remarks
        Service->>DB: Update request and cascade device state
    end

    Gate->>API: GET /guard and /{id}/devices
    API->>DB: Read v_active_event_requests and v_event_device_status
    Gate->>API: POST /devices/log-entry or /log-exit
    API->>Service: Validate approved request and active dates
    Service->>DB: INSERT event_device_logs
    Gate->>API: PUT /devices/{eventDeviceId}/verify
    Service->>DB: Set manifest device_status = returned
